    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels. The single gap (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted because the single ASTM F1717 compression-bending condition is the primary and most critical COU scenario, directly supported by the regulatory test protocol, and the shortfall is offset by the high relevance and rigor of all other factors. The FEA ensemble demonstrates consistent predictive capability across three independent modeling teams and two experimental laboratories. The credibility package is accepted as sufficient to support the regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
